OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1783682372
OL,3,CFriend of 16-year-old boy stabbed saw
OL,4,Cattacker 'with no hesitation', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FJoshua had been at the train station
OL,8,Fwith a friend, who gave evidence on
OL,9,FWednesday describing how he was tapped
OL,10,Fon the shoulder by the teenager
OL,11,Faccused of murder.
OL,13,FHe asked "Is that Josh?" before he
OL,14,Fstepped ahead of him, pulled a knife
OL,15,Ffrom his right hip and "went for it
OL,16,Ftwice" and ran.
OL,26,@uD@JOUuD@XO]wD@XOUxD@FO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
