OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1783682372
OL,3,CFriend of 16-year-old boy stabbed saw
OL,4,Cattacker 'with no hesitation', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThe prosecution allege the trio
OL,8,F"plotted and planned" the stabbing
OL,9,Fattack over an unpaid #20 cannabis
OL,10,Fdebt.
OL,12,FSnapchat messages from the months
OL,13,Fbefore read in court included the
OL,14,Fteenager accused of murder saying:
OL,15,F"Josh will perish if I don't get my
OL,16,Fmoney, that's a fact and he knows this.
OL,18,F"I'm ready to sit in a prison cell for
OL,19,F30 years over a #20 sheet."
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@UO]wD@AOUzD@AOU{D@[O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1783682372
OL,3,CFriend of 16-year-old boy stabbed saw
OL,4,Cattacker 'with no hesitation', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FAddressing the jury after the
OL,8,Fprosecution opening, the 16-year-old
OL,9,Fdefendant's lawyer Colin Aylott KC
OL,10,Fsaid the principle issue between the
OL,11,Fprosecution and defence case is one of
OL,12,Fintent.
OL,14,FThe youth has pleaded guilty to
OL,15,Fmanslaughter but the prosecution
OL,16,Fasserts he is guilty of murder,
OL,17,Falleging he intended to cause "really
OL,18,Fserious harm".
OL,26,@yD@_OUzD@MO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1783682372
OL,3,CFriend of 16-year-old boy stabbed saw
OL,4,Cattacker 'with no hesitation', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThe defence said their case is the 16-
OL,8,Fyear-old only intended to cause "some
OL,9,Fharm".
OL,11,FEvidence of the messages in the lead
OL,12,Fup to the attack, the prosecution
OL,13,Falleges, show his "true intent", Mr
OL,14,FAylott said.
OL,16,FBut he said: "The defence will assert
OL,17,Fa mix of fantasy, hyped up teen
OL,18,Fexaggeration or the straight out lies
OL,19,Fof an immature young man trying to
OL,20,Fimpress his friends."
OL,26,@pD@aOUqD@EO]uD@SOUuD@_O]xD@NOU|D@UO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1783682372
OL,3,CFriend of 16-year-old boy stabbed saw
OL,4,Cattacker 'with no hesitation', court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FThe defence also disputes all the
OL,8,Fmessages specifically relate to Joshua
OL,9,Fin the case.
OL,11,FDefence counsel for the 15-year-old
OL,12,Fyouth also invited the jury to
OL,13,Fconsider whether the messages were of
OL,14,F"bravado" or "definite agreement" and
OL,15,Fasked for the messages to be seen in
OL,16,Fproper context.
OL,18,FThe trial continues.
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@IO]vD@NOUvD@aO]
